comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T13:34:18.933Z",cursor-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search telemetry analysis skill collected user data --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Reusing telemetry epic pm-lnq3 as parent; net-new child task because no active item covers persisted telemetry analysis plus remote skill creation."
  "2026-04-26T13:53:08.123Z",cursor-agent,"Completed persisted telemetry analysis and remote skill installation. Remote skill files are at /home/steve/container/pm-cli/skills/pm-telemetry-analysis with SKILL.md, scripts/analyze_telemetry.py, and references/schema.md. Aggregate report snapshot saved at /home/steve/container/pm-cli/docs/TELEMETRY_PRODUCT_ANALYSIS_2026-04-26.md. Report snapshot analyzed 11219 non audit-smoke events across 1341 installations, 5624 sessions, and 75 commands; linked smoke check later saw 11243 analyzed events, confirming live telemetry continued to persist during this work."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T13:53:15.326Z",cursor-agent,"Product-improvement findings from aggregated telemetry: update command has high failure rate driven by close-through-update and audit ownership restrictions; calendar today alias and aggregate status grouping are repeated user expectations; search has high p95 latency; telemetry payload lacks explicit pm CLI version and source classification, making real-user versus automation segmentation harder."
